<li id="cite_note-CathEnc1910_Catholic-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="Roman_Catholics#cite_ref-CathEnc1910_Catholic_24-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="Roman_Catholics#cite_ref-CathEnc1910_Catholic_24-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFThurston1908" class="citation encyclopaedia"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herbert_Thurston" title="Herbert Thurston">Thurston, Herbert</a> (1908). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/03449a.htm">"Catholic"</a>.  In <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knight" title="Knight">Knight, Kevin</a> (ed.). <i>The Catholic Encyclopedia</i>. <b>3</b>. New York: Robert Appleton Company<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">17 August</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Catholic&amp;rft.btitle=The+Catholic+Encyclopedia&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Robert+Appleton+Company&amp;rft.date=1908&amp;rft.aulast=Thurston&amp;rft.aufirst=Herbert&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newadvent.org%2Fcathen%2F03449a.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACatholic+Church" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r951705291"/></span>
